    correct_answer: { ids: ['a'] },
    rationale: 'During a PTSD nightmare/flashback, orient the patient with calm, simple statements about safety and present reality. "You\'re safe, you\'re in the hospital" grounds the patient. Dismissing the experience or leaving is non-therapeutic; detail-seeking during acute distress is re-traumatizing.',
