    correct_answer: { ids: ['d'] },
    rationale: 'AAP recommends introducing solid foods around 6 months with signs of readiness: sitting with support, good head control, interest in food, loss of tongue-thrust reflex. Iron-fortified single-grain cereals and pureed vegetables/fruits are appropriate first foods.',
