    rationale: 'Red flags for abuse: bruises in multiple healing stages (different-colored), patterned injuries (burns, bite marks, belt shapes), inconsistent history. Bruises on shins/knees and bony prominences are normal in active toddlers. Mandated reporters must report ALL suspected abuse.',
