    correct_answer: { ids: ['b'] },
    rationale: 'DKA in a child: hyperglycemia + vomiting + Kussmaul breathing (metabolic acidosis compensation) = pediatric emergency. IV access for fluid resuscitation (normal saline) and continuous IV insulin are priorities. Oral carbs worsen hyperglycemia; glucagon treats hypoglycemia.',
